<TITLE> Policeman caught for attempted mugging </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  An assistant sub-inspector of police was arrested in the capital on Tuesday on charges of attempted mugging. Moinul Hossain has been closed to the Adabor Police Station while the police are looking for the two other accused, Rawshan Zaman, sub-inspector of Kotwali Police Station, and Detective Branch constable Saju Mia. Assistant police commissioner of Motijheel zone Mahfuzul Islam told bdnews24.com two staffs, 'Sujon' and 'Liton', working in the mobile shop of Saqlain Ahmed at Motaleb Plaza, were heading to Kakrail on a rickshaw from Motijheel to deposit Tk 16.50 lakh at a bank. They were stopped by three men on a motor cycle at a crossing. He said, according to the staffs, the passengers identifying themselves as DB police claimed the money in their possession was illegal. The staffs protested and passers-by and on-duty policemen gathered there. Two of the motorcycle riders escaped but Hossain was caught. The amount recovered from the spot was Tk 15.92 lakh though the businessman said there was Tk 16.50 lakh. Police are preparing to file a case, the official added. bd
